FBIS4-688 "drafr072_c_94018" FBIS-AFR-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Former Ciskei Party Election Candidates Withdraw Former Ciskei Party Election Candidates Withdraw MB1304114494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1035 GMT 13 Apr 94 MB1304114494 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Report by G. van Oudtshoorn] [Text] Bisho April 13 SAPA -- Four prominent members of former Ciskei military ruler Brig Oupa Gqozo's African Democratic Movement [ADM] have withdrawn as candidates for the elections, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reoported on Wednesday. ADM Publicity Secretary Vuyani Mati confirmed the resignations from the movement, naming the men as: Ciskei Department of Information Assistant Director Namba Sebe; ADM's former Publicity Secretary Vuyo Magodla; Ciskei consul general in Johannesburg Mthetheleli Taba; and Department of Information Acting Director Nolwandle Ngxizela. Earlier this week Ciskei's joint administrators announced that employed political candidates would have to take unpaid leave during the election period.
